INTRO: WHY SHAREBITE EXISTS
Every day, shops throw away food. Restaurants bin full trays of leftovers. People have old jackets and kids’ clothes that no longer fit. Yet down the road, someone’s cold. Someone’s hungry.

This isn’t a lack-of-resources problem. It’s a connection problem.

ShareBite solves that. It’s a simple, mobile-first platform that connects people who have extra — with people who genuinely need help.

No middleman. No paperwork. Just help, fast.

THE VISION
To create a community-powered donation network that gives every South African the power to reduce hunger and waste in their own neighborhood — using just their phone.

HOW IT WORKS
When you open ShareBite, it’s simple:
“Hi Thapelo — are you donating or receiving today?”

Choose a path.
If you’re donating: fill in what you have (e.g. “3 loaves of bread” or “Size 7 winter jacket”).
If you’re receiving: type what you need (“Jacket for 7-year-old boy”).

No heavy forms. No wasted time.

FEATURES (MVP)

Email/password login (Firebase Auth)

Role-based UI flow (Donor or Recipient)

Smart toggles: Individual or Business donors

Simple Donation Form (item, type, optional note)

Lightweight Request Form (what, size/age/gender if needed)

Recipient Dashboard: view latest donations

Clean, responsive UI (Material Design 3)

TECH STACK

Flutter – UI & Mobile Development

Firebase Auth – Secure login & roles

Cloud Firestore – Realtime data storage

Material Design 3 – Beautiful, minimal UI

FlutterFire CLI – Backend setup & integration

TARGET USERS

